<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="top-n">top <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /tɒp/    美 /tɑːp/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>顶端；末梢；表面：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>at the top</strong> of a mountain 
在山顶</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>the tops of the trees 
树梢</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>polish the top of the table 
擦亮桌面</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>最高或最重要的级别或位置：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She is <strong>at the top of</strong> her class in French.
她的法语在班上名列前茅。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="on-top">on top</h3>
<p>1.<strong>在上方；领先地：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Stand on top and look down. 
站在顶上俯视。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Who will come out on top, I wonder? 
我想，谁会得第一呢？</p><footer>北师大④ – 11</footer></div>

<h3 id="on-top-of">on top of</h3>
<p>1.<strong>在…之上；加之：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>That high mountain has a tower on top of it. 
那座高山顶上有一座塔。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He gave me a meal and, on top of that, money for my journey. 
他管了我一顿饭，除此之外，还给了我路费。</p></div></div>